📚 Campus Club Management Suite
1. Overview
The Campus Club Management Suite is a web-based platform that digitizes student club operations and fosters inter-college collaboration.
It enables students to create and manage clubs, organize events, publish achievements, and interact with like-minded peers.
This project is being developed for a hackathon, focusing on fast prototyping while demonstrating innovation, tech implementation, and usability.
________________________________________
2. Problem Statement
Currently, student clubs face challenges such as:
•	Lack of digital tools for managing members and events
•	Difficulty tracking participation and achievements
•	Limited collaboration opportunities across colleges
Our solution: A centralized web application where students and clubs can manage everything digitally — from events to forums to inter-college collaborations.
________________________________________
3. Core Features
🎭 Club Management
•	Create, browse, and join clubs (Sports, Robotics, Arts, Coding, etc.)
•	Club Admin dashboard: manage members, approve new join requests, schedule events
📅 Event & Activity Tracker
•	Event calendar with RSVP system
•	Track attendance and participation
•	Analytics dashboard (participation rate, most active clubs)
📰 News & Announcements
•	Post achievements and updates (like a campus newspaper)
•	Highlight inter-college events and competition wins
💬 Discussion Forums
•	Club-specific forums for discussions
•	Inter-college collaboration board
•	Like, comment, and reply features
🏅 Gamification & Badges
•	Award badges for participation (e.g., Active Member, Event Organizer, Club Leader)
•	Leaderboard for active contributors
📊 Member Analytics Dashboard
•	Individual profile with joined clubs, attended events, badges earned
•	Club analytics: number of members, events organized, impact score
